      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E_rel or validation metric) computed for hemolysis index at all operating points; uncertainty intervals overlap assessed.",
      "rationale": "Relative error computed at all five points; mean E_rel = 18% on absolute hemolysis index. Experimental uncertainty bars overlap CFD predictions at three of five points. Systematic over-prediction at high-speed conditions noted."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Hemolysis index QoI directly maps to clinical threshold metric; no surrogate QoI substitution without justification.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) used as primary QoI, which is the clinically accepted metric. Mapping from CFD shear stress to NIH uses Power-Law model — a known approximation with limited validation at high shear rates above 500 Pa."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
